      },
      "how": {
        "title": "How are memories created?",
        "desc": "When you chat with the AI assistant, the system automatically records raw events, then uses an LLM to extract structured memory items. Each memory has a confidence score â€” the higher the score, the more reliable the information."
      },
      "status": {
        "title": "Memory status explained",
        "desc": "Shadow: Memory is stored but not injected into conversations (default). Active: Memory is automatically recalled in relevant conversations. Disabled: Manually turned off. Expired: Past its time-to-live."
      },
      "manage": {
        "title": "How to manage memories?",
        "desc": "In the Memory Items tab, you can view, edit, or delete memories. You can change a memory's status (e.g. promote from Shadow to Active), adjust importance, and set expiration. The Statistics tab provides an overview of all memory data."
